        <header>
            <div class="logo-container">
                <div class="logo">
                    
                    <div class="logo-subtext">REMEDIAL HEALTH SOLUTIONS</div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <h1>Pharmaceutical Warehouse Quarantine Management</h1>
            <p class="subtitle">Operation Department</p>
        </header>
        
        <div class="content">
            <!-- Slide 1 -->
            <div class="slide active">
                <div class="card">
                    <h2><i class="fas fa-info-circle"></i> Introduction to Quarantine Management</h2>
                    <p>Product quarantine is a critical quality control process in pharmaceutical warehousing designed to prevent mixing of approved products with those not yet released, suspected to be defective, or rejected. This systematic approach ensures compliance with regulatory standards and protects patient safety.</p>
                    
                    <div class="visual-representation">
                        <i class="fas fa-boxes" style="font-size: 4rem; color: #0053a1;"></i>
                        <p class="caption">Pharmaceutical products in quarantine storage</p>
                    </div>
                    
                    <p>Effective quarantine management involves physical segregation, clear labeling, systematic controls, and detailed documentation to maintain product integrity throughout the supply chain.</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="card">
                    <h2><i class="fas fa-clipboard-list"></i> Key Learning Objectives</h2>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Understand the purpose and regulatory requirements of quarantine management</li>
                        <li>Identify the different status zones in a pharmaceutical warehouse</li>
                        <li>Execute proper procedures for incoming and internal quarantine processes</li>
                        <li>Recognize and apply correct labeling protocols</li>
                        <li>Understand WMS processes and guidelines</li>
                        <li>Differentiate between physical and electronic quarantine systems</li>
                        <li>Monitor key performance metrics (KPIs)</li>
                        <li>Understand Nigerian regulatory requirements</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <!-- Slide 2 -->
            <div class="slide">
                <div class="card">
                    <h2><i class="fas fa-exclamation-triangle"></i> Importance of Quarantine Management</h2>
                    <p>Proper quarantine procedures are essential for multiple reasons that impact patient safety, regulatory compliance, and business operations.</p>
                    
                    <div class="info-grid">
                        <div class="info-item">
                            <h3><i class="fas fa-user-md"></i> Patient Safety</h3>
                            <p>Prevents compromised, adulterated, or counterfeit medications from reaching patients, directly impacting health outcomes.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="info-item">
                            <h3><i class="fas fa-gavel"></i> Regulatory Compliance</h3>
                            <p>Mandated by WHO, NAFDAC and other regulatory bodies under Good Distribution Practices (GDP) guidelines.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="info-item">
                            <h3><i class="fas fa-shield-alt"></i> Quality Assurance</h3>
                            <p>Maintains product integrity throughout the supply chain from manufacturer to end-user.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="info-item">
                            <h3><i class="fas fa-building"></i> Business Protection</h3>
                            <p>Prevents financial losses from recalls, regulatory actions, and reputational damage.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="visual-representation">
                        <i class="fas fa-balance-scale" style="font-size: 4rem; color: #0053a1;"></i>
                        <p class="caption">Regulatory compliance is a critical aspect of pharmaceutical operations</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <!-- Slide 3 -->
            <div class="slide">
                <div class="card">
                    <h2><i class="fas fa-map-marked-alt"></i> Three Status Zones System</h2>
                    <p>Pharmaceutical warehouses must maintain clear physical or virtual separation between products with different statuses.</p>
                    
                    <div class="status-zones">
                        <div class="zone quarantine-zone">
                            <h3>QUARANTINE ZONE</h3>
                            <p><i class="fas fa-warehouse"></i> Yellow Coding</p>
                            <p>Holding area for goods pending quality decision</p>
                            <p>Restricted access</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="zone released-zone">
                            <h3>RELEASED ZONE</h3>
                            <p><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> Green Coding</p>
                            <p>Area for stock approved by QA for sale</p>
                            <p>Regular access for picking</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="zone rejected-zone">
                            <h3>REJECTED ZONE</h3>
                            <p><i class="fas fa-times-circle"></i> Red Coding</p>
                            <p>Area for failed stock awaiting destruction/return</p>
                            <p>Restricted access with special procedures</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="visual-representation">
                        <i class="fas fa-warehouse" style="font-size: 4rem; color: #0053a1;"></i>
                        <p class="caption">Visual representation of status zones in a pharmaceutical warehouse</p>
                    </div>
                    
                    <p>Every product must exist in one, and only one, of these states at any given time. Movement between zones requires formal authorization and documentation.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <!-- Slide 4 -->
            <div class="slide">
                <div class="card">
                    <h2><i class="fas fa-tasks"></i> Incoming Goods Quarantine Process</h2>
                    <p>A step-by-step procedure for handling newly received pharmaceutical products:</p>
                    
                    <div class="process-steps">
                        <div class="step">
                            <div class="step-number">1</div>
                            <div class="step-content">
                                <strong>Receive and Inspect</strong>
                                <p>Check shipment integrity, temperature monitors, and documentation upon arrival</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="step">
                            <div class="step-number">2</div>
                            <div class="step-content">
                                <strong>Immediate Transfer</strong>
                                <p>Move to designated quarantine area without delay - never leave on receiving dock</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="step">
                            <div class="step-number">3</div>
                            <div class="step-content">
                                <strong>Apply Labeling</strong>
                                <p>Attach clear quarantine labels with all required information</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="step">
                            <div class="step-number">4</div>
                            <div class="step-content">
                                <strong>System Update</strong>
                                <p>Change status in Warehouse Management System (WMS) to "QUARANTINE"</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="step">
                            <div class="step-number">5</div>
                            <div class="step-content">
                                <strong>Notify QA</strong>
                                <p>Inform Quality Assurance department for inspection and testing</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="step">
                            <div class="step-number">6</div>
                            <div class="step-content">
                                <strong>Await Decision</strong>
                                <p>Hold until formal release or reject instruction is received from QA</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="visual-representation">
                        <i class="fas fa-clipboard-check" style="font-size: 4rem; color: #0053a1;"></i>
                        <p class="caption">Documentation is critical at each step of the process</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <!-- Slide 5 -->
            <div class="slide">
                <div class="card">
                    <h2><i class="fas fa-tags"></i> Quarantine Labeling Requirements</h2>
                    <p>Proper labeling is essential for effective quarantine management and preventing errors:</p>
                    
                    <div class="label-examples">
                        <div class="label-card correct">
                            <h3><i class="fas fa-check"></i> Correct Labeling</h3>
                            <div class="label-content">
                                <strong style="color: #dc3545; font-size: 1.2em;">QUARANTINE</strong><br>
                                Product: Med-X 100mg Tablets<br>
                                Batch No.: XZ-47821<br>
                                Quantity: 5000 Tablets<br>
                                Manufacturer: PharmaCorp Inc.<br>
                                Date Received: 2023-10-26<br>
                                Reason: Incoming Inspection<br>
                                Reference ID: QRN-2023-1056<br>
                                Storage: 15-25°C
                            </div>
                            <p class="caption" style="margin-top: 10px;">Clear, comprehensive, and standardized</p>
                        </div>
                        
                        <div class="label-card incorrect">
                            <h3><i class="fas fa-times"></i> Incorrect Labeling</h3>
                            <div class="label-content">
                                Handwritten note: "Don't use - maybe bad?"<br><br>
                                No product details<br>
                                No batch information<br>
                                No date or reference ID<br>
                                Not conspicuous or standardized<br>
                                Unclear instructions
                            </div>
                            <p class="caption" style="margin-top: 10px;">Vague, incomplete, and prone to error</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="visual-representation">
                        <i class="fas fa-tag" style="font-size: 4rem; color: #0053a1;"></i>
                        <p class="caption">Example of a proper quarantine label with all required information</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <!-- Slide 6: WMS Process and Guidelines -->
            <div class="slide">
                <div class="card">
                    <h2><i class="fas fa-desktop"></i> WMS Process and Guidelines</h2>
                    <p>The Warehouse Management System (WMS) is critical for effective quarantine management:</p>
                    
                    <div class="process-steps">
                        <div class="step">
                            <div class="step-number">1</div>
                            <div class="step-content">
                                <strong>Automated Status Assignment</strong>
                                <p>WMS automatically assigns "QUARANTINE" status to all incoming goods upon receipt</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="step">
                            <div class="step-number">2</div>
                            <div class="step-content">
                                <strong>Location Management</strong>
                                <p>System directs operatives to place goods in designated quarantine locations</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="step">
                            <div class="step-number">3</div>
                            <div class="step-content">
                                <strong>Task Generation</strong>
                                <p>WMS automatically generates QA inspection tasks with priority levels</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="step">
                            <div class="step-number">4</div>
                            <div class="step-content">
                                <strong>Electronic Hold</strong>
                                <p>System prevents any transactions for quarantined items (picking, transfer, etc.)</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="step">
                            <div class="step-number">5</div>
                            <div class="step-content">
                                <strong>Status Change Authorization</strong>
                                <p>Only authorized QA personnel can change status from QUARANTINE to RELEASED or REJECTED</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="step">
                            <div class="step-number">6</div>
                            <div class="step-content">
                                <strong>Audit Trail</strong>
                                <p>System maintains complete digital record of all status changes with timestamps and user IDs</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="visual-representation">
                        <i class="fas fa-server" style="font-size: 4rem; color: #0053a1;"></i>
                        <p class="caption">WMS provides digital controls and audit trails for quarantine management</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <!-- Slide 7: Physical vs. Electronic Quarantine -->
            <div class="slide">
                <div class="card">
                    <h2><i class="fas fa-compress-arrows-alt"></i> Physical vs. Electronic Quarantine</h2>
                    <p>Our quarantine system uses both physical and digital controls to prevent mistakes:</p>
                    
                    <table class="comparison-table">
                        <tr>
                            <th>Aspect</th>
                            <th>Physical Quarantine</th>
                            <th>Electronic Quarantine</th>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td><strong>Primary Control</strong></td>
                            <td>Physical separation in designated areas</td>
                            <td>Digital status in WMS</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td><strong>Visual Indicators</strong></td>
                            <td>Colored zones, signage, labels</td>
                            <td>Status flags in system, screen colors</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td><strong>Access Control</strong></td>
                            <td>Restricted physical access</td>
                            <td>Role-based system permissions</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td><strong>Error Prevention</strong></td>
                            <td>Physical barriers prevent accidental mixing</td>
                            <td>System blocks invalid transactions</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td><strong>Documentation</strong></td>
                            <td>Paper logs, physical signatures</td>
                            <td>Electronic audit trails, digital signatures</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td><strong>Strengths</strong></td>
                            <td>Immediately visible, doesn't rely on technology</td>
                            <td>Automated controls, comprehensive tracking</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <td><strong>Limitations</strong></td>
                            <td>Requires space, manual processes</td>
                            <td>Dependent on system availability</td>
                        </tr>
                    </table>
                    
                    <div class="visual-representation">
                        <i class="fas fa-shield-alt" style="font-size: 4rem; color: #0053a1;"></i>
                        <p class="caption">Dual controls provide redundancy and enhance security</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <!-- Slide 8: Key Performance Metrics (KPIs) -->
            <div class="slide">
                <div class="card">
                    <h2><i class="fas fa-chart-line"></i> Key Performance Metrics (KPIs)</h2>
                    <p>Monitoring these KPIs helps ensure effective quarantine management:</p>
                    
                    <div class="kpi-grid">
                        <div class="kpi-item">
                            <h3>Quarantine to Release Time</h3>
                            <p>Average time from receipt to QA release decision</p>
                            <p><strong>Target: < 24 hours</strong></p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="kpi-item">
                            <h3>Quarantine Accuracy</h3>
                            <p>Percentage of items correctly quarantined</p>
                            <p><strong>Target: 100%</strong></p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="kpi-item">
                            <h3>Labeling Compliance</h3>
                            <p>Percentage of quarantined items with correct labeling</p>
                            <p><strong>Target: 100%</strong></p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="kpi-item">
                            <h3>Temperature Excursions</h3>
                            <p>Number of temperature-sensitive products with storage violations</p>
                            <p><strong>Target: 0</strong></p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="kpi-item">
                            <h3>Return Processing Time</h3>
                            <p>Average time to process returned goods through quarantine</p>
                            <p><strong>Target: < 24 hours</strong></p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="kpi-item">
                            <h3>QA Decision Accuracy</h3>
                            <p>Percentage of correct release/reject decisions</p>
                            <p><strong>Target: 100%</strong></p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="visual-representation">
                        <i class="fas fa-chart-bar" style="font-size: 4rem; color: #0053a1;"></i>
                        <p class="caption">Regular KPI monitoring ensures continuous improvement</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <!-- Slide 9: Case Study -->
            <div class="slide">
                <div class="card">
                    <h2><i class="fas fa-book-open"></i> Case Study: Effective Recall Management</h2>
                    <p><strong>Situation:</strong> Nationwide recall of "Med-X 100mg" tablets (Batch: XY-12345) due to potential contamination.</p>
                    
                    <div class="case-study">
                        <h3>Challenges</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Batch distributed to 150+ pharmacies across the region</li>
                            <li>Time-sensitive recall with patient safety implications</li>
                            <li>Need to identify and isolate all affected stock quickly</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="process-steps">
                        <div class="step">
                            <div class="step-number">1</div>
                            <div class="step-content">
                                <strong>Immediate Action</strong>
                                <p>Within 15 minutes of recall notice, QA placed electronic hold on the batch in WMS</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="step">
                            <div class="step-number">2</div>
                            <div class="step-content">
                                <strong>Physical Identification</strong>
                                <p>Warehouse team located all physical stock using WMS location data</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="step">
                            <div class="step-number">3</div>
                            <div class="step-content">
                                <strong>Quarantine Implementation</strong>
                                <p>All identified stock moved to rejection zone with updated labeling</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="step">
                            <div class="step-number">4</div>
                            <div class="step-content">
                                <strong>Documentation</strong>
                                <p>Complete audit trail maintained for regulatory reporting</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="case-study">
                        <h3>Results</h3>
                        <ul>
                            <li>100% of affected batch identified and isolated within 2 hours</li>
                            <li>Zero distribution of recalled product after notification</li>
                            <li>Complimentary feedback from regulatory inspectors</li>
                            <li>Enhanced reputation for reliability and patient safety</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <!-- Slide 10: Regulatory Bodies in Nigeria -->
            <div class="slide">
                <div class="card">
                    <h2><i class="fas fa-landmark"></i> Regulatory Bodies in Nigeria</h2>
                    <p>Pharmaceutical operations in Nigeria must comply with these key regulatory agencies:</p>
                    
                    <div class="regulatory-grid">
                        <div class="regulatory-item">
                            <h3><i class="fas fa-building"></i> NAFDAC</h3>
                            <p><strong>National Agency for Food and Drug Administration and Control</strong></p>
                            <p>Primary regulator for pharmaceuticals, food, and medical devices</p>
                            <p>Mandates Good Distribution Practice guidelines</p>
                            <p>Conducts inspections and issues operating licenses</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="regulatory-item">
                            <h3><i class="fas fa-tablets"></i> PCN</h3>
                            <p><strong>Pharmacists Council of Nigeria</strong></p>
                            <p>Regulates pharmacy practice and personnel</p>
                            <p>Sets standards for pharmaceutical care</p>
                            <p>Licenses pharmaceutical premises and personnel</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="regulatory-item">
                            <h3><i class="fas fa-hospital"></i> FMOH</h3>
                            <p><strong>Federal Ministry of Health</strong></p>
                            <p>Develops national health policies and regulations</p>
                            <p>Oversees implementation of national drug policies</p>
                            <p>Coordinates with international health organizations</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="regulatory-item">
                            <h3><i class="fas fa-capsules"></i> NDPC</h3>
                            <p><strong>National Drug Policy and Control</strong></p>
                            <p>Develops and implements national drug policies</p>
                            <p>Monitors drug availability and affordability</p>
                            <p>Combats counterfeit and substandard medicines</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="visual-representation">
                        <i class="fas fa-file-contract" style="font-size: 4rem; color: #0053a1;"></i>
                        <p class="caption">Compliance with Nigerian regulations is mandatory for all operations</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <!-- Slide 11: Summary and Q&A -->
            <div class="slide">
                <div class="summary-section">
                    <h2><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> Key Takeaways Summary</h2>
                    
                    <div class="key-points">
                        <div class="key-point">
                            <h3><i class="fas fa-shield-alt"></i> Patient Safety First</h3>
                            <p>Quarantine processes are designed to protect patients from compromised medications.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="key-point">
                            <h3><i class="fas fa-clipboard-list"></i> Strict Compliance</h3>
                            <p>Adherence to NAFDAC, PCN, and other regulatory requirements is non-negotiable.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="key-point">
                            <h3><i class="fas fa-warehouse"></i> Three-Zone System</h3>
                            <p>Clear segregation between Quarantine, Released, and Rejected zones is essential.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="key-point">
                            <h3><i class="fas fa-tags"></i> Proper Labeling</h3>
                            <p>Clear, comprehensive labeling prevents errors and ensures traceability.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="key-point">
                            <h3><i class="fas fa-desktop"></i> Dual Controls</h3>
                            <p>Both physical and electronic quarantine systems provide redundancy and security.</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="key-point">
                            <h3><i class="fas fa-chart-line"></i> Performance Monitoring</h3>
                            <p>Regular KPI tracking ensures continuous improvement in quarantine processes.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="qa-section">
                    <h2><i class="fas fa-question-circle"></i> Questions & Answers</h2>
                    
                    <div class="qa-item">
                        <div class="question"><i class="fas fa-question"></i> What should I do if I find a product in the wrong zone?</div>
                        <div class="answer">Immediately move it to the correct zone, update the WMS status, and notify your supervisor. Document the incident in the deviation log.</div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="qa-item">
                        <div class="question"><i class="fas fa-question"></i> How long can products stay in quarantine?</div>
                        <div class="answer">Products should not remain in quarantine for more than 5 business days. Escalate to QA if a decision is pending beyond this timeframe.</div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="qa-item">
                        <div class="question"><i class="fas fa-question"></i> Who is authorized to change quarantine status in the WMS?</div>
                        <div class="answer">Only trained QA personnel have authorization to change product status from Quarantine to Released or Rejected.</div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="qa-item">
                        <div class="question"><i class="fas fa-question"></i> What information must be on a quarantine label?</div>
                        <div class="answer">Product name, batch number, quantity, date received, reason for quarantine, reference ID, and storage requirements if applicable.</div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
